1
00:00:06,006 --> 00:00:07,841
Is Jae-seok taking a dump?

2
00:00:09,050 --> 00:00:10,593
Do you think he's constipated?

3
00:00:13,555 --> 00:00:15,724
JAE-SEOK'S BEEN IN THE BATHROOM
FOR 15 MINUTES

4
00:00:15,807 --> 00:00:17,726
That's one thing,
but what if he passed out?

5
00:00:17,809 --> 00:00:19,185
What if he pushed too hard?

6
00:00:19,686 --> 00:00:21,521
"YU JAE-SEOK PASSES OUT
IN BATHROOM FROM OVERWORK"

7
00:00:21,604 --> 00:00:24,024
Should we go look, just in case?
It's been quite a while.

8
00:00:24,107 --> 00:00:25,025
GETTING GENUINELY WORRIED

9
00:00:25,108 --> 00:00:26,860
- Yeah, it's been a while.
- Let's check on him.

10
00:00:26,943 --> 00:00:28,611
- Should we go check on him?
- You're right,

11
00:00:28,695 --> 00:00:30,280
he should've been back by now.

12
00:00:30,363 --> 00:00:33,408
CHECKING IN A HURRY

13
00:00:35,952 --> 00:00:38,038
Jae-seok! Hyung!

14
00:00:38,538 --> 00:00:39,622
Oh.

15
00:00:39,706 --> 00:00:41,541
Jae-seok! Hyung!

16
00:00:42,292 --> 00:00:43,376
Yeah.

17
00:00:43,460 --> 00:00:45,879
Yeah.

18
00:00:45,962 --> 00:00:47,630
FORTUNATELY,
THEY CAN HEAR HIS VOICE

19
00:00:47,714 --> 00:00:49,758
- What?
- Nothing, hyung. We were just…

20
00:00:49,841 --> 00:00:52,761
It's legit.

21
00:00:52,844 --> 00:00:54,387
RELIEVED, BACK TO WAITING

22
00:00:54,471 --> 00:00:55,722
- He's fine.
- For real?

23
00:00:56,264 --> 00:00:57,474
- I think--
- Where are you going?

24
00:00:57,557 --> 00:00:59,476
We thought you might've passed out.
You'd been awhile.

25
00:00:59,559 --> 00:01:00,852
THE YOUNGER ONES TALK ABOUT
HOW SCARED THEY WERE

26
00:01:00,935 --> 00:01:02,395
We thought you passed out while pooping.

27
00:01:02,479 --> 00:01:06,024
No, it was just talking to Ye-eun
about it… I felt the call of nature.

28
00:01:06,858 --> 00:01:08,985
We were worried. We thought
you passed out because you were so tired.

29
00:01:09,069 --> 00:01:10,612
- You thought I passed out?
- We were worried about you.

30
00:01:10,695 --> 00:01:12,655
No, I feel great right now.
I feel like I could fly.

31
00:01:14,866 --> 00:01:15,992
THE GUEST IS KING AND SO AM I

32
00:01:16,076 --> 00:01:18,119
- They're back.
- I can hear them.

33
00:01:18,203 --> 00:01:19,412
- We're home!
- We're back!

34
00:01:19,496 --> 00:01:20,872
THE GUESTS RETURN
TO JAE-SEOK'S B&B

35
00:01:20,955 --> 00:01:22,665
- Hello, Jae-seok's B&B!
- Home sweet home.

36
00:01:22,749 --> 00:01:24,000
- We're back!
- We've got tomatoes!

37
00:01:24,084 --> 00:01:25,668
- We're here!
- How was it? What's all this?

38
00:01:25,752 --> 00:01:27,087
WELCOMING THE GUESTS

39
00:01:27,170 --> 00:01:28,379
WELCOMING THEM FROM THE KITCHEN

40
00:01:28,463 --> 00:01:30,006
- Man, that's a lot!
- Wow.

41
00:01:30,090 --> 00:01:31,549
Did you take a lot of photos?

42
00:01:31,633 --> 00:01:32,967
Look at that.

43
00:01:33,051 --> 00:01:34,511
- This one looks great.
- Don't we look like real farmers?

44
00:01:34,594 --> 00:01:36,054
LOOKING AT THE PHOTOS
FROM THE TOMATO FARM

45
00:01:36,137 --> 00:01:37,680
- This one's a killer.
- We look like pros!

46
00:01:37,764 --> 00:01:40,016
- Wow.
- And we got that special just for you.

47
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:41,392
- Thank you.
- The photos look great.

48
00:01:41,476 --> 00:01:43,603
HEART-SHAPED TOMATO

49
00:01:43,686 --> 00:01:45,897
- Wow, they're twins. Like a heart.
- A heart. It's a heart.

50
00:01:46,481 --> 00:01:47,482
- So cute.
- You see?

51
00:01:48,108 --> 00:01:49,109
It's too cute to eat.

52
00:01:49,609 --> 00:01:51,111
You picked a lot of them. Yeah.

53
00:01:51,486 --> 00:01:53,738
STILL, WE HAVE TO TRY IT

54
00:01:54,405 --> 00:01:55,532
You want to split it with me?

55
00:01:55,615 --> 00:01:57,033
Wow.

56
00:01:57,117 --> 00:01:58,868
SPLITTING
THE HEART-SHAPED TOMATO

57
00:01:58,952 --> 00:01:59,953
That's special.

58
00:02:01,579 --> 00:02:02,705
Mmm, tasty.

59
00:02:02,789 --> 00:02:03,998
- I'm so happy.
- Have you tried the tomatoes?

60
00:02:04,082 --> 00:02:05,125
- Not yet.
- Oh.

61
00:02:05,208 --> 00:02:06,709
You all gave them to Woo-seok.

62
00:02:06,793 --> 00:02:07,877
Wait a second. Wait!

63
00:02:07,961 --> 00:02:09,671
Hey, you know what, it's fine.

64
00:02:09,754 --> 00:02:12,090
Really, I don't want to eat it
if I have to beg for it.

65
00:02:12,173 --> 00:02:13,883
You were all giving them
to Woo-seok, not me.

66
00:02:13,967 --> 00:02:15,468
No, we saved some for you here.

67
00:02:15,552 --> 00:02:17,971
QUICKLY GIVING KWANG-SOO
A TOMATO

68
00:02:18,054 --> 00:02:22,016
- Mmm. Oh, it's so good. It's really good.
- I know right.

69
00:02:23,726 --> 00:02:25,603
Hey, here come the others!

70
00:02:25,687 --> 00:02:27,438
Wow.

71
00:02:27,522 --> 00:02:29,399
Wow!

72
00:02:29,482 --> 00:02:30,692
TEAM SWEET POTATO
& TEAM RADISH ALSO RETURN

73
00:02:30,775 --> 00:02:32,694
Check it out!
We brought back some radishes.

74
00:02:32,777 --> 00:02:34,362
- Oh, really?
- You got radishes?

75
00:02:34,445 --> 00:02:35,446
- Yeah.
- Radishes!

76
00:02:36,447 --> 00:02:37,782
- You need a hand?
- Good work, guys.

77
00:02:37,866 --> 00:02:39,576
- Okay, let's put it down here.
- Look at that.

78
00:02:39,659 --> 00:02:40,660
- Radishes.
- Wow.

79
00:02:40,743 --> 00:02:42,745
You harvested these yourselves,
so you should take them home.

80
00:02:42,829 --> 00:02:43,788
- Yeah.
- Great idea.

81
00:02:43,872 --> 00:02:45,331
- That's super heavy.
- Let's wash them.

82
00:02:45,415 --> 00:02:46,624
- Just the tomatoes…
- And the radishes…

83
00:02:46,708 --> 00:02:47,709
There's so much.

84
00:02:47,792 --> 00:02:49,502
- Wash them before you take them home.
- Yeah.

85
00:02:49,586 --> 00:02:51,796
Radishes are expensive. I used to be one.

86
00:02:52,714 --> 00:02:53,715
Oh, right.

87
00:02:53,798 --> 00:02:54,966
BACK IN HER RADISH DAYS

88
00:02:55,049 --> 00:02:57,385
- Then you should take some home.
- You do look like one.

89
00:02:57,468 --> 00:02:58,469
It's not that.

90
00:02:59,554 --> 00:03:01,806
- What are you talking about?
- I don't look like it.

91
00:03:01,890 --> 00:03:03,892
That wasn't what you meant?

92
00:03:03,975 --> 00:03:06,477
- I used to dress like a radish.
- Oh.

93
00:03:07,395 --> 00:03:08,813
What are you saying?

94
00:03:10,023 --> 00:03:11,316
What do you mean I look like one?

95
00:03:11,399 --> 00:03:13,067
- Well, he means you resemble…
- Well, I mean…

96
00:03:13,151 --> 00:03:14,319
- Get a nice one.
- Wait, let me…

97
00:03:14,903 --> 00:03:15,904
That one looks good.

98
00:03:20,533 --> 00:03:21,534
It's your vibe.

99
00:03:22,452 --> 00:03:23,953
You think that's my vibe?

100
00:03:24,495 --> 00:03:25,580
Ah, that's hilarious.

101
00:03:25,663 --> 00:03:27,081
- We got it, don't worry.
- Give me a minute

102
00:03:27,165 --> 00:03:28,750
- to go switch into my sandals.
- If you say so.

103
00:03:28,833 --> 00:03:30,627
- Yeah, just relax.
- We should wash these too.

104
00:03:30,710 --> 00:03:33,129
- We'd better get the grills going now.
- Got it.

105
00:03:33,213 --> 00:03:35,465
You must be getting hungry
after all that work, right?

106
00:03:35,548 --> 00:03:36,549
Yeah.

107
00:03:36,633 --> 00:03:39,010
We're going to start grilling
the meat now, so go get ready.

108
00:03:39,093 --> 00:03:40,094
WHAT'S FOR DINNER TODAY?

109
00:03:40,178 --> 00:03:41,930
- Change your shoes and stuff.
- Oh, okay.

110
00:03:42,013 --> 00:03:44,849
TODAY'S MENU
BARBECUE PARTY

111
00:03:44,933 --> 00:03:45,934
- Put these on top.
- Hang on.

112
00:03:46,017 --> 00:03:47,602
Don't you think these gloves
are too small for us?

113
00:03:47,685 --> 00:03:48,686
WHO'S IN CHARGE
OF THE MAIN DISH?

114
00:03:48,770 --> 00:03:49,771
We'll try em.

115
00:03:49,854 --> 00:03:50,855
THE DOOR BROTHERS

116
00:03:50,939 --> 00:03:52,690
- Should we wear two layers?
- One's enough.

117
00:03:53,191 --> 00:03:54,567
+ FIRE STARTERS

118
00:03:54,859 --> 00:03:56,152
+ BRIQUETTES

119
00:03:56,611 --> 00:03:57,779
+ LUMP CHARCOAL

120
00:03:58,071 --> 00:03:59,572
READY TO START THE FIRE,
NICE AND SIMPLE

121
00:04:01,574 --> 00:04:04,994
STARTING THE FIRE

122
00:04:05,078 --> 00:04:06,829
Hyung, should I add more charcoal?

123
00:04:07,330 --> 00:04:08,498
No, we're good.

124
00:04:10,041 --> 00:04:12,460
HOT

125
00:04:13,378 --> 00:04:14,671
STIFF

126
00:04:14,754 --> 00:04:16,673
Wow, this is kinda tricky.

127
00:04:16,756 --> 00:04:17,757
No.

128
00:04:18,299 --> 00:04:19,592
It'll take half an hour?

129
00:04:20,426 --> 00:04:21,427
Sounds right.

130
00:04:23,096 --> 00:04:24,597
- Are you sure you've done this?
- Yeah.

131
00:04:24,681 --> 00:04:25,807
DOUBTING HIS EXPERIENCE

132
00:04:25,890 --> 00:04:27,600
- How long will it take?
- Not too much longer.

133
00:04:29,102 --> 00:04:30,895
This is why I don't like barbecues.

134
00:04:32,689 --> 00:04:34,691
Do you go camping with your kids?

135
00:04:35,024 --> 00:04:36,985
SHAKING HIS HEAD

136
00:04:37,068 --> 00:04:40,113
I know I should, but…

137
00:04:41,155 --> 00:04:43,366
WHILE WAITING
FOR THE FIRE TO BE LIT

138
00:04:46,327 --> 00:04:48,121
YE-EUN PREPS THE SIDE DISHES

139
00:04:50,999 --> 00:04:52,041
Ye-eun, is the rice done?

140
00:04:52,125 --> 00:04:53,584
- Oh, yeah, it's done.
- Yeah?

141
00:04:53,668 --> 00:04:56,170
- We should give it a stir then.
- I was letting it steam for a bit.

142
00:04:56,254 --> 00:04:57,255
LETTING IT STEAM

143
00:04:57,338 --> 00:04:58,339
- Let me know when it's done.
- Okay.

144
00:04:58,423 --> 00:05:00,091
Man, once you start, there goes the day.

145
00:05:00,174 --> 00:05:02,260
- Right? That's what moms always say.
- Man.

146
00:05:02,343 --> 00:05:05,096
They're like, "Just eat what I give you."

147
00:05:05,179 --> 00:05:06,597
Well, now I get what that means.

148
00:05:06,681 --> 00:05:07,849
- Yeah.
- It must be really hard,

149
00:05:07,932 --> 00:05:09,892
- deciding what to make every day.
- Seriously.

150
00:05:09,976 --> 00:05:11,602
- Now I get it.
- Yeah, I get my mom.

151
00:05:11,686 --> 00:05:12,687
- Yeah, totally.
- Mmm.

152
00:05:12,770 --> 00:05:14,022
FINALLY UNDERSTANDING
HOW THEIR MOMS FELT

153
00:05:14,105 --> 00:05:16,816
By the way, Ye-eun,
you seem to be doing well health-wise.

154
00:05:17,525 --> 00:05:18,818
Yeah, things are okay right now…

155
00:05:18,901 --> 00:05:21,529
- Yeah, you can't tell you were ever sick.
- Yeah, hopefully it's over!

156
00:05:21,612 --> 00:05:22,739
YE-EUN HAS RECOVERED SO WELL,

157
00:05:22,822 --> 00:05:24,032
YOU WOULDN'T EVEN KNOW
SHE WAS SICK

158
00:05:24,782 --> 00:05:26,826
- That's a relief.
- Yeah, truly.

159
00:05:26,909 --> 00:05:28,578
It's such a relief.

160
00:05:29,287 --> 00:05:30,747
- Of course.
- Seriously.

161
00:05:31,289 --> 00:05:35,043
I mean, they say even a tumor
as small as a tenth of a centimeter

162
00:05:35,126 --> 00:05:37,503
can spread.
So it was definitely a possibility.

163
00:05:37,587 --> 00:05:38,588
Exactly.

164
00:05:40,298 --> 00:05:42,133
And they said there was quite a lot…

165
00:05:43,551 --> 00:05:44,552
of the cancer.

166
00:05:44,635 --> 00:05:45,845
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

167
00:05:45,928 --> 00:05:47,388
I'm glad you're okay now.

168
00:05:47,889 --> 00:05:48,890
I really am, Ye-eun.

169
00:05:48,973 --> 00:05:51,476
I'm so grateful for that. Truly.

170
00:05:51,559 --> 00:05:52,560
Be grateful.

171
00:05:52,643 --> 00:05:54,395
- You should be grateful for everything.
- Yeah.

172
00:05:55,104 --> 00:05:56,397
Done yet?

173
00:05:57,523 --> 00:05:59,609
NOT YET

174
00:06:01,778 --> 00:06:03,488
By the way, look at Joo-hyun!

175
00:06:04,364 --> 00:06:05,656
She must run hot!

176
00:06:05,740 --> 00:06:07,950
- Short sleeves again?
- It's cold enough to see your breath.

177
00:06:08,284 --> 00:06:10,286
TUCKED DEEP IN THE MOUNTAINS,
THE B&B FEELS EVEN COLDER

178
00:06:10,370 --> 00:06:11,454
CURRENT TEMPERATURE 13°C

179
00:06:11,996 --> 00:06:14,248
BUT IT'S STILL SUMMER
FOR JOO-HYUN

180
00:06:14,791 --> 00:06:17,085
CHUGGING COLD WATER

181
00:06:17,168 --> 00:06:18,461
Wow, that's amazing.

182
00:06:20,880 --> 00:06:22,590
So for example, take Joo-hyun…

183
00:06:22,673 --> 00:06:24,300
A THOUGHT CROSSED HIS MIND
WHEN HE SAW JOO-HYUN

184
00:06:24,384 --> 00:06:28,346
I could say, here's an award for you,
Joo-hyun, for saving so many lives.

185
00:06:29,639 --> 00:06:30,765
SOUNDS LAME

186
00:06:30,848 --> 00:06:32,100
What, is that lame?

187
00:06:33,434 --> 00:06:34,310
SUDDENLY TALKING ABOUT AWARDS

188
00:06:34,394 --> 00:06:35,895
I've been thinking about it a lot,

189
00:06:35,978 --> 00:06:37,105
and before this ends,

190
00:06:37,188 --> 00:06:40,066
I would really like to find some way
we might be able to show the guests

191
00:06:40,149 --> 00:06:41,776
how grateful we are to have them all here.

192
00:06:41,859 --> 00:06:43,986
Something to acknowledge that we see them,

193
00:06:44,070 --> 00:06:45,905
and how hard they're working
in their own lives.

194
00:06:46,906 --> 00:06:49,409
- She runs hot…
- The Hot Girl Award.

195
00:06:49,909 --> 00:06:51,411
Because it can mean a few things.

196
00:06:51,494 --> 00:06:53,871
She runs hot,
and she's also really passionate.

197
00:06:53,955 --> 00:06:55,289
"For passionately saving lives,

198
00:06:55,373 --> 00:06:57,625
- we present to you the Hot Girl Award."
- Yeah, "For saving lives,

199
00:06:57,708 --> 00:07:00,461
- we present to you the Hot Girl Award."
- Joo-hyun gets the Hot Girl Award. Okay.

200
00:07:00,545 --> 00:07:02,922
- Kwang-soo. You know, for Joo-hyun?
- Yeah.

201
00:07:03,005 --> 00:07:05,007
- The "Hot Girl Award".
- Oh.

202
00:07:05,091 --> 00:07:06,676
- She always…
- 'Cause she's in T-shirts?

203
00:07:06,759 --> 00:07:07,760
- Yeah.
- Sounds good.

204
00:07:08,678 --> 00:07:09,679
Well…

205
00:07:09,762 --> 00:07:10,805
IDEAS KEEP POURING IN

206
00:07:10,888 --> 00:07:12,640
"The Three Beauties Award" sounds good.

207
00:07:12,723 --> 00:07:15,393
- The three of them. Ae-yeong and…
- Hyeong-seon and Eun-jung.

208
00:07:15,476 --> 00:07:16,561
Yeah, Eun-jung.

209
00:07:16,644 --> 00:07:19,147
- How about "The Three Amigo-Angels" award?
- Huh?

210
00:07:19,230 --> 00:07:20,565
- "The Three Amigo-Angels."
- "The Three Amigo-Angels"?

211
00:07:20,648 --> 00:07:21,649
Because they're all…

212
00:07:21,732 --> 00:07:23,359
- That's cute.
- Good idea.

213
00:07:23,901 --> 00:07:26,279
- You know what? Forget it.
- What?

214
00:07:28,656 --> 00:07:32,660
I'm too tired right now.
I want to do it, but I'm just too tired.

215
00:07:32,743 --> 00:07:33,744
FLIP-FLOPPER AWARD

216
00:07:33,828 --> 00:07:34,954
- I get it.
- We still…

217
00:07:35,037 --> 00:07:37,039
We still have way too many
to come up with.

218
00:07:38,332 --> 00:07:39,333
Is it ready?

219
00:07:40,543 --> 00:07:42,503
Come on, let me see. I think it's ready.

220
00:07:42,587 --> 00:07:43,963
YOU CAN START GRILLING
ONCE THE CHARCOAL TURNS WHITE

221
00:07:44,046 --> 00:07:45,131
It's ready. Wow, Kwang-soo…

222
00:07:45,214 --> 00:07:46,215
40 LONG MINUTES
AFTER STARTING THE FIRE

223
00:07:46,299 --> 00:07:47,842
…guess you have done this before.

224
00:07:47,925 --> 00:07:48,926
FINALLY SETTING UP THE GRILL

225
00:07:49,927 --> 00:07:52,138
I think we should start
with the pork belly.

226
00:07:52,763 --> 00:07:54,515
The fat will drip down
and get the fire going.

227
00:07:56,601 --> 00:07:58,186
Kwang-soo's good at this.

228
00:07:58,269 --> 00:07:59,812
Wow, hyung, the pork belly was

229
00:07:59,896 --> 00:08:00,980
- a great choice.
- Right?

230
00:08:01,063 --> 00:08:02,732
- Yeah.
- Hey, that looks good.

231
00:08:03,858 --> 00:08:06,277
- Can I help you with anything?
- Hmm?

232
00:08:06,861 --> 00:08:07,945
Ever done this, Minister?

233
00:08:08,029 --> 00:08:10,114
Oh, yeah,
every time I go on a church retreat.

234
00:08:10,198 --> 00:08:11,365
- Oh.
- Right.

235
00:08:11,449 --> 00:08:12,450
- Expert.
- Here.

236
00:08:12,533 --> 00:08:13,534
A MAX-LEVEL BBQ MASTER ENTERS

237
00:08:13,618 --> 00:08:15,703
- We've got an expert here.
- Yeah, we've got a pro.

238
00:08:15,786 --> 00:08:16,954
ONCE THE GRILL IS UP AND RUNNING

239
00:08:17,371 --> 00:08:19,207
THE SMELL OF MEAT
DRAWS THE GUESTS IN

240
00:08:20,917 --> 00:08:22,668
STARING

241
00:08:22,752 --> 00:08:23,878
I brought some garlic powder.

242
00:08:23,961 --> 00:08:25,546
- Should we sprinkle it on?
- Oh, sure.

243
00:08:25,630 --> 00:08:27,423
